{"english": 1, "name": "Catch Me If You Can", "duration": "2h 21min", "release_date": "25 December 2002 (USA)", "director": ["Steven Spielberg"], "scenarists": ["Jeff Nathanson", "Frank Abagnale Jr.", "DreamWorks", "Kemp Company", "Splendid Pictures"], "actors": ["Leonardo DiCaprio", "Tom Hanks", "Christopher Walken"], "type": ["Biography", "Crime", "Drama"], "ratings": ["8.1"], "brief_into": "New Rochelle, the 1960s. High schooler Frank Abagnale Jr. idolizes his father, who's in trouble with the IRS. When his parents separate, Frank runs away to Manhattan with $25 in his checking account, vowing to regain dad's losses and get his parents back together. Just a few years later, the FBI tracks him down in France; he's extradited, tried, and jailed for passing more than $4,000,000 in bad checks. Along the way, he's posed as a Pan Am pilot, a pediatrician, and an attorney. And, from nearly the beginning of this life of crime, he's been pursued by a dour FBI agent, Carl Hanratty. What starts as cat and mouse becomes something akin to father and son."}
