{"english": 1, "name": "The Perks of Being a Wallflower", "duration": "1h 42min", "release_date": "12 October 2012 (USA)", "director": null, "scenarists": ["Stephen Chbosky", "Stephen Chbosky", "Summit Entertainment", "Mr. Mudd"], "actors": ["Logan Lerman", "Emma Watson", "Ezra Miller"], "type": ["Drama", "Romance"], "ratings": ["8.0"], "brief_into": "Based on the novel written by Stephen Chbosky, this is about 15-year-old Charlie (Logan Lerman), an endearing and naive outsider, coping with first love (Emma Watson), the suicide of his best friend, and his own mental illness while struggling to find a group of people with whom he belongs. The introvert freshman is taken under the wings of two seniors, Sam and Patrick, who welcome him to the real world."}
