{"english": 1, "name": "The Shining", "duration": "2h 26min", "release_date": "13 June 1980 (USA)", "director": ["Stanley Kubrick"], "scenarists": ["Stephen King", "Stanley Kubrick", "Warner Bros.", "Hawk Films", "Peregrine"], "actors": ["Jack Nicholson", "Shelley Duvall", "Danny Lloyd"], "type": ["Drama", "Horror"], "ratings": ["8.4"], "brief_into": "Signing a contract, Jack Torrance, a normal writer and former teacher agrees to take care of a hotel which has a long, violent past that puts everyone in the hotel in a nervous situation. While Jack slowly gets more violent and angry of his life, his son, Danny, tries to use a special talent, the \"Shining\", to inform the people outside about whatever that is going on in the hotel."}
