{"english": 1, "name": "The Devil Wears Prada", "duration": "1h 49min", "release_date": "30 June 2006 (USA)", "director": ["David Frankel"], "scenarists": ["Aline Brosh McKenna", "Lauren Weisberger", "Fox 2000 Pictures", "Dune Entertainment", "Major Studio Partners"], "actors": ["Anne Hathaway", "Meryl Streep", "Adrian Grenier"], "type": ["Comedy", "Drama"], "ratings": ["6.8"], "brief_into": "In New York, the simple and naive just-graduated in journalism Andrea Sachs is hired to work as the second assistant of the powerful and sophisticated Miranda Priestly, the ruthless and merciless executive of the Runway fashion magazine. Andrea dreams to become a journalist and faces the opportunity as a temporary professional challenge. The first assistant Emily advises Andrea about the behavior and preferences of their cruel boss, and the stylist Nigel helps Andrea to dress more adequately for the environment. Andrea changes her attitude and behavior, affecting her private life and the relationship with her boyfriend Nate, her family and friends. In the end, Andrea learns that life is made of choices."}
